Titolo: The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past and Four Swords

Anno: 2002

Descrizione: The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past and Four Swords is an action-adventure game co-developed by Nintendo and Capcom and published by Nintendo for the Game Boy Advance. The game was released on December 2, 2002 in North America; on March 14, 2003 in Japan; and on March 28, 2003 in Europe. The cartridge contains a modified port of The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past, originally released for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System in 1991, and an original multiplayer-only game titled Four Swords, which serves as the 9th installment in The Legend of Zelda series.
A stand-alone port of Four Swords was released for a limited time on Nintendo's DSiWare service as The Legend of Zelda: Four Swords Anniversary Edition on September 28, 2011, which includes new content, such as a single-player mode and additional areas. It was re-released on the Nintendo 3DS eShop for a limited time from January 31 to February 2, 2014, in celebration of their then latest released game, The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds.



